cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.CV, cs.LG 

This paper deals with the control and stabilization of walking gaits in bipedal robots, which falls under the scope of robotics (cs.RO). The use of virtual constraints for coordination between joints suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the development of an algorithm for self-stabilization, which involves mathematical analysis and optimization, indicating a possible connection to machine learning (cs.MA), computer vision (cs.CV), and/or machine learning (cs.LG).
